
 This directory contains some small demo programs which show you how to use
some of the features BGUI has to offer. The following demos are available:

 Name:		Author:                 Description:
 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 BGUIDemo	Jan van den Baard	General demo for BGUI.
 ColorWheel	Jan van den Baard	A BGUI implementation of the Commodore
					colorwheel example.
 CXDemo         Jan van den Baard	A  small  "do-nothing"  example of the
					BGUI commodity class.
 FileReq	Jan van den Baard	A BGUI filereq class demonstration.
 IDCMPHook	Jan van den Baard	Shows a simple	IDCMP-hook  which will
					flash the display every two seconds.
 MultiCol	Jan van den Baard	A  demonstration  how  you can	code a
					multi-column   listview    with    the
					listview class hooks.
 Images         Jan van den Baard	A  demo of  using  standard  intuition
					images in the button class.
 StringHook	Jan van den Baard	Shows you  how	to  install  a	string
					object edit hook.
 MultiSelect	Jan van den Baard	Show  you  a  simple   multi-selection
					listview object.
 Backdrop	Jan van den Baard	A small demonstration  of a  backdrop,
					borderless BGUI window.
 Colors         Jan van den Baard	A  small  demonstration  how to change
					the background and label  colors of an
					object on the fly.
 MultiFont	Jan van den Baard	A simple demo showing  you how	to use
					several fonts in a single window.
 AddButtons	Paul Weterings		A demo of how to use the GRM_ADDMEMBER
					GRM_INSERTMEMBER   and	 GRM_REMMEMBER
					methods of the group class.

 -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 BGUIPlayer	Jan van den Baard	An   audio  CD	player	program  which
					should	  work	  with	 most	SCSI-2
					compatible CD-ROM drives.
 WallStreet	Jan van den Baard	A complete commodities Exchange clone.
